chapter.verse:


If anyone sins in that he hears a public 


adjuration to testify, and though he is a witness, whether he has seen or come to know the matter, yet does not speak, he shall 


bear his iniquity;

or if anyone utters with his lips a 


rash oath to do evil or to do good, any sort of rash oath that people 


swear, and it is hidden from him, when he comes to know it, and he realizes his guilt in any of these;
